BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Fragmented Researcher
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Asher Mir
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: Left scarred by his encounter with the Vex, the irascible Asher Mir holds Io for the Vanguard... and science.

interactions.flavorLineOne: For the thoughtful gift, Asher offers as much gratitude as ever—which is to say very, very little.
Asher's right arm seems to twitch involuntarily toward the gift, but you can't be sure. He seems as thankful as ever.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Asher wishes to express his gratitude for your many exploits on Io. Meet with him in the Rupture.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Asher Mir

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Asher thanks you for the work you've done in securing Io.

New challenges appear on the horizon, however.

"The Festival of the Lost is not about masks and sweets," Asher says when you return. "You've known true loss, so you must know that."

After a contemplative pause, he hands you a stalk of celery. "Go on, then. Play your game, but don't let the levity of it fool you into forgetting what this tradition is truly about."

"Back again, eh? I like your tenacity. It will serve me as we continue to study interesting readings across this increasingly odd world… For science!"

Continue to explore Io by completing adventures, bounties, Lost Sectors, public events, and world quests to earn XP, gear, and other rewards.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Now that you've proven to be a valuable... assistant, Asher wishes to speak with you in the Rupture.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Asher Mir

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Asher thanks you for the significant progress you've made on Io.

Continue your adventures on the planet to earn his respect and rewards.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Asher thanks you for eliminating the annoyances from the Prison of Elders on Io.
headerDisplayProperties.name: FLASHPOINT: IO

interactions.flavorLineOne: Asher thanks you for eliminating the annoyances from the Prison of Elders on Io.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Asher is inspired by your heroism in victory, and wishes to speak with you in the Rupture.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Asher Mir

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Asher congratulates you on your victory over Ghaul.

While the head of the Red Legion has been slain, the Red War continues across the solar system.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Asher is more acquainted with death than most Guardians. But even he must be having a hard time after Cayde's passing.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Asher Mir

interactions.flavorLineOne: Asher is a scientist. He knows, better than most, that every action has an equal and opposite reaction. Whatever you choose to do, Asher just hopes you are ready to pay the price.
You cleared the Pyramidion of the Taken and prevented them from rebuilding their army. Asher refuses to thank you for doing your job.

The Taken have entered the Pyramidion, most likely looking to replenish their ranks following the Taken War. 

Investigate the Taken activity in the Pyramidion on Io.

We don't know enough about the Red Legion's flagship, the Almighty. Asher Mir believes that by gaining access to the Golden Age Warmind Network, we could retrieve important data to improve the odds of victory. 

Choose your exotic gear and find out the Almighty's weakness by completing mission FURY.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Ikora's agents have reported unusual Taken activity on the plateaus of Io. Confirm the intel.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Dynasty

interactions.flavorLineOne: Speak with Asher about the ramifications of the Vex being converted by the Taken.

"Another hero come to aid me in my research? Good. Good. Maybe the Vanguard isn't so single-minded after all."

Asher Mir offers Io bounties, quests, and various rewards for completing activities on Io.

Help Asher by challenging yourself with adventures, bounties, Lost Sectors, public events, and quests on Io. In return, you will be rewarded.

"Ah, unchocolate," Asher says, taking the chocolate bar. "An acquired taste, to be sure, but so much better than those cloying chocolate coins…"

He sets the bar down. "I don't approve of this pointless scavenger hunt of yours. It's easy to laugh at death when you believe you're never going to die, isn't it?"
Complete patrols and public events on Io to get Phaseglass Needles and earn rewards from Asher Mir.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
